race.comment: BOURBON ROAD (1) presents third up having placed in both runs back from a spell, trying hard behind a handy winner over this route last time out, running on nicely for second. Finds the right race here and rates highly. OLIVIA'S SCANDAL (8) is racing consistently well of late, trying hard over 1400m at Mildura last time out when beaten under a length into third. She drops sharply back to the 975m which is a query but she has placed over this route and can win. COSMIC VIXEN (3) was poor last time at Ballarat on heavy which can be excused but had won there on debut and is open to plenty of improvement. MISSED THE MARK (2) struggles to win but is going okay and can sneak into the finish. FLIP THE SWITCH (6) stuck on well at Pakenham last time and that reads well.
